The article is a statement from the President on the passing of Ed Koch. The President describes Koch as an extraordinary Mayor, irrepressible character, and quintessential New Yorker. Koch helped New York City achieve economic renewal, expand affordable housing, and extend opportunity to more people. The President also praises Koch's energy, force of personality, and commitment to causes such as civic issues and the security of Israel. The President sends his thoughts and prayers to Koch's loved ones and the city.